t class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 Infil vs a 50 Warrior</span><hr size=1> MinionX do you play an infiltrator, do you even play an assassin? 700 standing PA by an infiltrator at 45th level. At 50th level most infiltrators cant even hit 700 because of the damage cap, only us CS spec infiltrators go to 700+, most of the 45th level infiltrators would not be able to hit a PA for 700 even if you were 20 levels lower then him and sitting down, without an extra critical, because of the hard damage cap (extra criticals can exceed damage caps in case you didnt know).<br>
<br>
If you got hit with a 700 'while standing' by a yellow con infiltrator it's a fully buf botted infiltrator and an extra critical. I dont buff bot, so who knows what damages I 'could' do, but I think its a cheap tactic and refuse to argue the power of any class based on the buff bot practice.<br>
<br>
Also keep in mind the discussion was about 50 inf vs 50 warrior, that means epic armor and thats where my figures are coming from. Epic armor has a huge impact on the damage you do.<br>
<br>
As for something wrong with my character. Find me a thrust infiltrator that can normally PA a standing, even level, tank for 700 without being majorly buff botted and an extra critical, and I will be more then happy to consider the possibility that something is wrong with my character.<br>
<br>
As for your purge points, I stand corrected. I looked at it and thought I saw the poison tick stop working and then start again, which is why I thought he used purge. Course if he had used purge he would have dropped the stun as well, which didnt occur to me at the time.<br>
<br>
I agree with your stun comment. I am stunned almost 90% of the times I get killed. Stun from shield, stun from weapon, stun from spells, the curse for all of us meleers. Personally I dont mind weapon/shield stuns as atleast that guy had to get in my face, had to risk being within my reach to get it.<br>
<br>
Culdor<br>
