<br>
on low-yellow players (46-48) I may hit for 500. On low blues (41-43) i can hit my cap of 705. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uwindariachopsalot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Windaria Chopsalot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/02 12:17:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3532.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 Infil vs a 50 Warrior</span><hr size=1> In regards to the Infiltrator vrs warrior. He prolly did not even need to PA/CD,or to receive a stun from Dragon Fang or be buffed to win the fight. Toe to Toe a Thrust infiltrator vrs Slash Warrior without stuns. With both players being unbuffed and having max counter melee resistance (Max +slash for Inf, Max +thrust for warrior). A max hp Inf vrs a Max hp Warrior. Could result in a dead warrior. <br>
<br>
The reasons are...<br>
#1: Evade 35% damage mitigation for Inf, from parsing logs my warrior has around 1% damage mitigation from defenses.<br>
#2: Reactionary damage based upon 35% Evade<br>
#3: Melee type resistances reduces damage on both sides, thus poisen dot damage becomes more significant.<br>
#4: Being able to swap in poisened weapons<br>
<br>
Warrior: 16.2 x 5.5 = 89.1 +15% (2h mod) = 102 +25% (50 skill) = 127.5 +75% (Positional damage - Havoc) = 223 +15%(armour bonus) = 256 -10% (absorb) = 230 -26% (slash resistance = 170.2 -35% (evade rate) = 110/5.5(delay) = 20 DPS<br>
Warrior DPS Versus INF = 20DPS<br>
Warrior Vrs Inf = 1250 (inf hps)/20 = 62.5 seconds to kill Inf<br>
<br>
Infiltrator:<br>
Primary hand Reactionary: 16.1 x3.5 = 56 +25%(50 skill) = 70 +75% (reactionary damage) = 122 +15% (armour Bonus) = 140 -27% absorb = 102.2 - 26%(Thrust resist) = 75 -1% (defenses) = 74/3.5 = 21 -65% (35% occurance) = 7 DPS<br>
<br>
Primary hand anytime: 16.1 x3.5 = 56 +25%(50 skill) = 70 +50% (reactionary damage) = 105 +15% (armour Bonus) = 120 -27% absorb = 87 - 26%(Thrust resist) = 64 -1% (defenses) = 63/3.5 = 18 -35% (65% occurance) = 11 DPS<br>
<br>
Offhand damage:16.1 x3.5 = 56 +25%(50 skill) = 70 +15% (armour Bonus) = 80 -27% absorb = 58 - 26%(Thrust resist) = 42 -1% (defenses) = 41/3.5 = 11 -62.5% (37.5% occurance) = 4 DPS<br>
<br>
Poisen: level 45 dot 71/5 = 14 dps<br>
<br>
Inf total DPS = 36 DPS<br>
Inf Vrs Warrior: 1774 (iWar hps)/36 = 49 seconds to kill Warrior<br>
<br>
Keep swaping in prepoisened weapons and an Inf will beat a warrior Toe to toe. Also something to note the warrior used 11 styles (in their time to kill). This doesn't take endurance into consideration. 35% of the infiltrators styles would be low endurance versus medium for the warrior (warrior could only use 6 styles, 4 slaming with a large shield). Also remember this does not include PA/CD or Dragonfang having stun. Shield Slam does not have a to hit bonus, also it costs 33% Total endurance. Also this does not include envenorating poisen. The con debuff is variable though lowering max hps between 100-400 on the warrior. Because of offhand variabilitly it could very well offer no damage potential to the Inf.<br>
<br>
Damage for both the warrior and the Inf are low, I was using 125% damage as normal average. Modifiers such as Warrior Str or Inf dex modifying damage not included.<br>
<br>
If you take out poisen swapping, ignore stuns, hidden attacks, and factor in endurance usage. It is a fairly even fight toe to toe. I think when you add in the hidden attack and CD or a dragon fang stunning it leans towards the INF heavily. If the warrior purges and lands a zero bonus to hit shield stun, before CD. The Warrior might win, if the Inf does not swap in a poisen weapon or land a dragon fang after.<br>
<br>
Bottom line is Warriors are Gimped. There is no help in site either. I do think a Smart warrior, can beat a stupid Infiltrator. Unfortunatly the same can not be said when you compare max's between Warrior vrs Armsman or Warrior Vrs Hero. The scale is so off balance it's not even funny when your opponant has 250% damage advantage (thrust/polearm armsman) or 200% damage 30% hps advantage (Spear Hero w/ bulwinkle).<br>
<br>
Alot of Warriors think there great in PVE also. Which doesn't really help there case with Mythic. Unfortuantly after they leave our 30-40 dungeon,  they will not meet many piercing opponants to understand how gimped they are. Deskvu is an NPC uses a spear (lvl 51+). My level 48 SB (no epic armour) is a better tank than my 50 warrior against her. Leather has 13% advantage over chain against pierce/thrust, LA/poisen is approximatly 80% more damaging ( or +250%) vrs 1h + shield. Warrior has a 12% mitigation advantage (block/parry/evade). Warriors have a 19% hp advantage.<br>
<br>
